data.title: OKX Ventures invests in Aria Protocol to tokenize intellectual property assets, boosting liquidity and music rights investment.
data.description: OKX Ventures has recently made an investment in Aria Protocol with the goal of facilitating the integration of real-world intellectual property assets onto blockchain technology. This strategic partnership aims to boost liquidity and create new investment avenues for various forms of intellectual property, such as music rights. This collaboration is expected to transform the way intellectual property is managed and traded by leveraging blockchain technology. This investment signifies a significant step towards digitizing and tokenizing intellectual property assets, opening up exciting opportunities for investors.

data.title: Empire Life Q3 2025: Common shareholders' net income $93 million; EPS $94.60. Sales growth in insurance & investment. Segregated fund assets exceed $10 billion. CEO touts strong LICAT ratio.
data.description: Empire Life Insurance Company reported in Q3 2025 a common shareholders' net income of $93 million, down from $177 million in Q3 2024. Earnings per share stood at $94.60, compared to $179.88 in the previous year. The decrease in net income was attributed to a more favorable net investment and insurance finance result in the comparative period. Despite this, new sales and deposits showed growth, with segregated fund assets exceeding $10 billion. The Life Insurance Capital Adequacy Test ratio remained strong. Return on common shareholders' equity was 12.3%, and the LICAT total ratio was 145%. Overall, Empire Life's financial performance showcased steady growth with a robust capital base.

data.title: Forage and Zip team up to assist Americans affected by government shutdown by offering temporary no-fee installment payment option.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, in San Francisco, Forage and Zip revealed their initiative to offer a temporary installment payment option with no fees for eligible recipients as a response to the uncertainty regarding the November SNAP benefit and other government funding. This plan aims to ensure continued access to essential resources for individuals in need during this time.

data.title: Little market impact after Trump-Xi trade truce meeting. Tech and global markets drop, with QQQ down 1% and China ETFs slipping. Full story on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Investors showed little reaction to Trump-Xi trade truce meeting in South Korea, with markets unaffected as the agreement lacked substance and surprises. The Invesco QQQ Trust dropped 1%, led by Meta Platforms Inc. which plunged 10% due to a surge in AI-related spending. China-exposed stocks also fell, with the Invesco China Technology ETF down 1.9% and iShares China Large-Cap ETF slipping 1.7%. Chinese tech ADRs in New York saw declines, with Alibaba falling 2.77%, PDD Holdings down 1.34%, JD.com sliding 2.43%, Baidu losing 3.71%, and Li Auto also facing losses. Fed Chair Jerome Powell's hawkish remarks and mixed earnings contributed to tech and global markets declining on Thursday.

data.description: Truxton Trust Company is excited to share that Jeffrey M. Laborde has recently been appointed to its Board of Directors.

data.title: Artesian Resources Corp boosts quarterly dividend by 2%, marking 4% increase for the year. Dividend now $0.3136 per share.
data.description: Artesian Resources Corporation (Nasdaq: ARTNA) based in Newark, Delaware, disclosed on October 30, 2025, that its Board of Directors greenlit a 2% boost in the quarterly common stock dividend, totaling a 4% increase for the year. This decision will elevate the quarterly dividend to $0.3136 per share on both Class A and Class B Common Stock. Shareholders of record by the end of business day on November 14, 2025, will receive the payment on November 24, 2025, lifting the yearly dividend rate to $1.2544 per share.

data.title: Fabrice Canonge appointed CEO of Centric Software by Dassault Systèmes board of directors on Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: Dassault Systèmes, the parent company of Centric Software, has recently revealed the naming of Fabrice Canonge as the new Chief Executive Officer of Centric Software. This decision was made by the board of directors and marks a significant change in leadership for the company. Fabrice Canonge's appointment as CEO was announced on October 30, 2025, and solidifies his role within the Dassault Systèmes organization. Canonge's new position underscores a strategic move by the company to steer its core brand, Centric Software, towards future growth and success.

data.title: ISM announces 2025-2026 Board of Directors in Tempe, Arizona, comprising top global executives.
data.description: Tempe, Arizona - On October 30, 2025, the Institute for Supply Management® (ISM®) unveiled its Board of Directors for the 2025-2026 term. The board comprises top global executives from various functional areas. The announcement was made during the Annual ISM Membership Meeting held in Tempe, Arizona on August 28, 2025.

data.title: Benzinga unveils 2025 Fintech Day & Awards agenda with top executives and investors in Detroit.
data.description: In Detroit on October 30, 2025, a well-known financial media and data company, Benzinga, revealed the schedule for the 2025 Fintech Day & Awards event. The agenda includes prominent figures such as executives, investors, and innovators from key fintech firms. This event aims to showcase the impact and advancements within the industry.

data.title: MG Properties buys Dockside Apartments in Kent, WA for $95.6M. Acquisition adds premier multifamily community.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, MG Properties, a privately owned real estate investment firm based in San Diego, proudly revealed their purchase of Dockside Apartments. This luxurious multifamily complex is located within the esteemed Lakes at Kent master planned community.

data.title: Ezee Fiber expands in Des Moines and Puyallup, with construction started after service launch in Kent. #FTTH #expansion
data.description: Just days after launching services in Kent, Washington, Ezee Fiber, a swiftly growing internet service provider with 100% fiber-to-the-home capability, declared the initiation of construction for its advanced fiber network in Des Moines. The announcement was made on October 30, 2025, in Houston.

data.title: Samaritan's Purse sends 38,000 lbs of relief supplies and Disaster Response Team to Jamaica post Hurricane Melissa.
data.description: In Boone, North Carolina, on October 30, 2025, it was reported that shortly after Hurricane Melissa hit Jamaica as a Category 5 hurricane, Samaritan's Purse took action by sending a Disaster Assistance Response Team (DART) and over 38,000 pounds of crucial relief supplies to aid the affected areas.

data.title: UofL researchers use external electrical stimulation to help paralyzed children walk; innovation for spinal cord injuries.
data.description: A groundbreaking development at the University of Louisville in Louisville, KY on Oct. 30, 2025, involved using an innovative external electrical stimulation technique to help children suffering from total paralysis caused by spinal cord injuries. Researchers at UofL's Kosair for Kids Center discovered that this technique enabled these children to regain the ability to take steps. This advancement is seen as a significant breakthrough in the field of pediatric rehabilitation and provides new hope for patients facing severe spinal cord injuries.

data.title: Lavazza partners with NYU Tisch School of the Arts to support the Martin Scorsese Virtual Production Center lounge.
data.description: Italian coffee brand Lavazza reaffirms its dedication to supporting the arts by partnering with the lounge at the Martin Scorsese Virtual Production Center at NYU Tisch in New York. On October 30, 2025, Lavazza made this announcement, emphasizing their continued commitment to entertainment and creative endeavors. This collaboration highlights Lavazza's ongoing initiative to promote cultural initiatives and artistic innovation. The partnership with the prestigious NYU Tisch center establishes a strong connection between Lavazza and the artistic community, showcasing their support for the industry.

data.title: City Ventures final sales release at Melodia in El Cajon; 29 townhomes, military buyers benefit from 0% down payment VA loans.
data.description: Located in El Cajon, California, City Ventures has launched the final sales release of Melodia, a community consisting of 29 new townhomes. The homes are designed with timeless and classic architecture, appealing to buyers looking for style. Positioned in a suburban, walkable neighborhood in El Cajon, Melodia offers convenient access to shopping and dining options. This development by City Ventures, known for building environmentally responsible homes with solar features, has generated significant interest among homebuyers.
